<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US" prefix="og:http://ogp.me/ns#">
  <head>
    <meta content="text/html;charset=utf-8" http-equiv="Content-Type" />
    <meta
    name="viewport"
    content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no"
    />
    <% include!("styles.stpl"); %>
    <meta name="description" content="Upload File or image" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Upload File" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <title>Upload File</title>
    <style>
      code {
        display: inline;
        background: var(--bg-darker);
      }
      span {
        font-style: italic;
      }
      @media(max-width: 600px) {
        .content-container {
            height: calc(100vh - 30px);
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="content-container">
      <h1 class="title">Upload File or Image</h1>
      <p>After successfully uploading the file, you will be directed back to the home page.</p>
      <p>you can reference files inside of notes by using the following link syntax, <code>&lsqb;&lsqb;files:&lt;filename&gt;&rsqb;&rsqb;</code></p>
      <p>If you are uploading a file named, <span>report.pdf</span>, you can reference it via <code>&lsqb;&lsqb;files:report.pdf&rsqb;&rsqb;</code></p>
      <p>Wiki syntax (using <code>&lsqb;&lsqb;link text|link location&rsqb;&rsqb;</code>) around the page you want to link is applicable here as well. In the previous example, if you wanted to link the report with the link text <span>this report</span>, you could do so with <code>&lsqb;&lsqb;this report|files:report.pdf&rsqb;&rsqb;</code></p>
      <form class="editor visible" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data" action="upload" target="_parent">
        <div class="uploader" data-text="Choose a file to upload">
          <label for="file">File</label>
          <input name="file" type="file" />
        </div>
        <button class="submit" type="submit">Upload</button>
      </form>
    </div>
    <% include!("footer.stpl"); %>
    <script>
      const filenameDisplay = document.querySelector("[data-text='Choose a file to upload']");
      const fileInput = document.querySelector("input");
      fileInput.addEventListener("change", e => {
              const filename = e.target.value.replace(/^.*?([^\\\/]*)$/, '$1');
              filenameDisplay.dataset.text = filename
            })
    </script>
  </body>
</html>

